  "title": "Logistics Operations Analyst",
  "description": "<h2>Job Description</h2><p>We are looking for a <strong>Logistics Operations Analyst</strong> to support and analyse logistics and supply chain operations. The role involves data analysis, operational reporting, process improvement, and coordination with internal teams and logistics partners to improve efficiency and performance.</p><p>This position requires strong analytical skills, structured problem-solving ability, and a good understanding of logistics operations.<br /></p><h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><h3>Logistics Operations Support</h3><ul><li><p>Monitor and support daily logistics operations including transportation, warehousing, and inventory movement</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with internal teams, vendors, and logistics partners to ensure smooth operations</p></li><li><p>Track shipment status, delivery timelines, and service performance</p></li></ul><h3>Data Analysis & Reporting</h3><ul><li><p>Collect, analyse, and interpret logistics and operational data</p></li><li><p>Prepare daily, weekly, and monthly operational reports</p></li><li><p>Track key performance indicators (KPIs) such as delivery performance, turnaround time, and operational efficiency</p></li><li><p>Identify operational issues and recommend improvement actions</p></li></ul><h3>Process Improvement</h3><ul><li><p>Assist in reviewing and improving logistics workflows and standard operating procedures (SOPs)</p></li><li><p>Support cost control and productivity improvement initiatives</p></li><li><p>Participate in process optimisation and digitalisation projects</p></li></ul><h3>Systems & Documentation</h3><ul><li><p>Maintain accurate operational records and reports using Excel and logistics systems</p></li><li><p>Update data related to inventory, transportation, and operations</p></li><li><p>Ensure proper documentation and compliance with company procedures<br /></p><h2>Requirements</h2><h3>Qualifications</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Bachelor’s Degree (Faculty of Science)</strong> in a relevant discipline such as Applied Science, Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Industrial Science, or equivalent</p></li></ul><h3>Experience</h3><ul><li><p>Relevant experience or strong knowledge in logistics operations, supply chain, or operations analysis</p></li><li><p>Fresh graduates with strong analytical capability and relevant training may be considered</p></li></ul><h3>Skills & Competencies</h3><ul><li><p>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Excel and data analysis</p></li><li><p>Good communication and coordination skills</p></li><li><p>Able to work independently and manage multiple tasks</p></li><li><p>Detail-oriented and well-organised</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
